This paper deals with transfer learning in Reinforcement Learning, which is a subfield of Machine Learning. The paper proposes a new credit assignment mechanism based on self-attention, which is a technique commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Computer Vision (CV), both of which fall under the category of Artificial Intelligence (AI). The paper also discusses the application of credit assignment in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of language models (cs.CL) to evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed credit assignment mechanism. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CL.
